it gets really dirty.</i>

22:52.093 --> 22:53.660
Fuck, can I open yet?

22:53.662 --> 22:55.896
Yes. Okay.

22:57.533 --> 22:59.966
Okay.

22:59.968 --> 23:02.002
This is nice. It is nice.

23:02.004 --> 23:04.570
You're right..

23:07.642 --> 23:09.875
Cheers.

23:17.284 --> 23:19.284
God.

23:27.293 --> 23:29.527
What if I moved to Montauk?

23:35.035 --> 23:36.400
Why?

23:37.503 --> 23:39.069
To be with you.

23:40.806 --> 23:44.641
No. I, I want a divorce, Noah.

23:44.643 --> 23:45.909
- Come on.
- Yeah.

23:45.911 --> 23:48.011
- You don't.
- Yeah.

23:48.013 --> 23:49.446
I do.

23:51.550 --> 23:53.383
Look.

23:53.385 --> 23:55.385
I know I was a jerk, but I...

23:57.655 --> 23:59.989
I just got out of three years in prison.

23:59.991 --> 24:03.392
I don't want what I used to.

24:03.394 --> 24:04.694
I just want a simple life.

24:04.696 --> 24:06.696
I just want to get back into teaching.

24:06.698 --> 24:08.965
I want to live with someone I love.

24:10.702 --> 24:14.035
Raise a... a kid that's not mine.

24:22.512 --> 24:24.679
All I thought about when I was away was

24:24.681 --> 24:26.615
all the time I wasted

24:26.617 --> 24:29.050
just chasing the wrong things,

24:29.052 --> 24:30.985
taking you for granted.

24:34.957 --> 24:36.356
You were the best thing
that ever happened to me.

24:36.358 --> 24:38.592
No. No, don't say that.

24:38.594 --> 24:40.728
- It's true.
- No, it's not.

24:40.730 --> 24:45.065
You're rewriting history.

24:45.067 --> 24:47.900
You and I were a mistake.

24:47.902 --> 24:48.901
- A mistake?
- Yeah.

24:48.903 --> 24:49.902
Come on.

24:49.904 --> 24:50.903
You know, you fell for me

24:50.905 --> 24:53.072
because you were bored

24:53.074 --> 24:56.976
and you felt trapped by Helen, your kids,

24:56.978 --> 24:59.345
your fucking father-in-law.

25:00.749 --> 25:02.214
And you wanted a fling,

25:02.216 --> 25:03.649
but you chose me,

25:03.651 --> 25:04.816
who had lost a child,

25:04.818 --> 25:07.418
and who was so incredibly sad

25:07.420 --> 25:10.522
you couldn't just abandon me,

25:10.524 --> 25:14.126
so you convinced yourself
that you loved me.

25:14.128 --> 25:16.461
And I convinced myself that I loved you,

25:16.463 --> 25:21.231
because I so desperately needed
someone just to take me away.

25:27.540 --> 25:29.874
I used you.

25:29.876 --> 25:33.544
You used me too.

25:33.546 --> 25:36.180
That's what happened between us.

25:37.616 --> 25:39.115
You... you really think that?

25:39.117 --> 25:42.052
Yeah. I know it's true.

25:42.054 --> 25:44.854
And you do too.

25:47.292 --> 25:48.958
Boys, bring your stuff inside!

25:48.960 --> 25:50.426
Fuck.

25:52.230 --> 25:55.864
Stop! Hey, get back here!

25:57.501 --> 25:58.801
I'm calling the cops!

25:58.803 --> 26:00.836
No. Shit.

26:00.838 --> 26:02.971
Fuck.

26:05.976 --> 26:09.044
You should've seen your fucking face.

26:09.046 --> 26:12.046
Hey! Hey!

26:12.048 --> 26:13.380
Fuck.

26:14.718 --> 26:16.584
- My God.
- Shh, shh, shh.

26:16.586 --> 26:19.220
God.

26:19.222 --> 26:20.521
Assholes.

26:20.523 --> 26:22.824
I'm gonna freak out.

26:22.826 --> 26:25.059
I'm fucking freezing.

26:27.263 --> 26:28.262
Fuck.

26:28.264 --> 26:29.763
Let's get you inside.

26:29.765 --> 26:31.497
No, look, I just want to go home, actually.

26:31.499 --> 26:32.565
Please.

26:36.371 --> 26:38.171
- Fuck!
- What?

26:38.173 --> 26:39.940
My fucking shoes. I left them.

26:42.544 --> 26:44.344
Careful.

26:49.016 --> 26:50.549
- No.
- Shit.

26:50.551 --> 26:52.184
- Wait! Wait!
- No!

26:52.186 --> 26:53.385
No, no, no, no.

26:53.387 --> 26:55.955
- No!
- Hey! Please!

26:57.424 --> 26:58.758
Can he come back?

26:58.760 --> 26:59.725
No.

26:59.727 --> 27:00.960
When's the next ferry?

27:00.962 --> 27:03.094
That was the last one of the day, dude.

27:05.698 --> 27:07.531
I'm really sorry.

27:12.939 --> 27:14.739
No.

27:33.558 --> 27:35.926
Thank God. Are you open?

27:35.928 --> 27:37.593
Technically, no.

27:37.595 --> 27:39.996
The season ended a few days ago, but...

27:41.833 --> 27:43.565
Ed?

27:43.567 --> 27:46.235
Can we take someone in for the night?

27:46.237 --> 27:49.071
Do you have any clothes we can borrow?

28:12.795 --> 28:15.562
I'll sign the divorce papers.

28:17.499 --> 28:20.467
As soon as we get home.

28:20.469 --> 28:22.036
Thank you.

28:25.674 --> 28:28.107
I just want to say one thing, though.

28:32.814 --> 28:35.048
I did love you.

28:38.486 --> 28:41.187
Yeah, I fucked up, and maybe...

28:41.189 --> 28:45.157
maybe it was a mistake
from the start, but...

28:45.159 --> 28:46.925
it was love.

28:48.829 --> 28:50.795
At least it was for me.

28:50.797 --> 28:52.331
So don't...

28:55.635 --> 28:57.035
don't take it all away from me

28:57.037 --> 28:58.803
by saying it wasn't real.

29:06.412 --> 29:08.913
You may not want to remember me, but...

29:12.151 --> 29:14.919
I want to remember you, okay?

29:21.726 --> 29:23.293
Okay.

29:44.848 --> 29:49.684
So, I still don't understand
how this is supposed to work.

29:49.686 --> 29:52.554
I mean, are you just gonna wait around

29:52.556 --> 29:56.958
for Cole to finally let you have
custody of your own child back?

29:56.960 --> 29:58.426
No.

29:58.428 --> 30:00.861
There's a whole court procedure.

30:00.863 --> 30:02.630
Which he can circumvent if he wants to.

30:02.632 --> 30:04.565
Right.

30:14.776 --> 30:16.709
I left her, Noah.

30:20.149 --> 30:22.916
I left her for six months. I...

30:27.455 --> 30:29.721
I'm not okay.

30:29.723 --> 30:34.393
You know, I mean, I'm
trying to be, but I...

30:36.397 --> 30:39.098
I have these moments of,

30:39.100 --> 30:42.301
like, such darkness.

30:44.637 --> 30:48.340
I don't know how I'll get past them.

30:55.949 --> 30:59.951
I just... I seem to be
making one bad decision

30:59.953 --> 31:03.587
after another.

31:09.595 --> 31:10.694
You know, maybe it's me.

31:10.696 --> 31:13.930
Maybe I'm just kidding myself

31:13.932 --> 31:18.601
if I think I could ever be a good mother.

31:23.608 --> 31:25.941
My mother...

31:27.945 --> 31:30.946
she couldn't give me everything I needed

31:30.948 --> 31:32.882
'cause she was sick.

31:35.819 --> 31:38.220
And as it got worse, she...

31:42.292 --> 31:44.359
I mean, she couldn't
help me with my homework.

31:44.361 --> 31:45.727
She couldn't teach me how to drive.

31:45.729 --> 31:47.329
She couldn't go shopping.

31:47.331 --> 31:50.899
She couldn't even...

31:50.901 --> 31:52.699
she couldn't even make a meal for me.

31:52.701 --> 31:54.868
But none of that mattered to me.

31:54.870 --> 31:57.804
I just needed to know she was there.

32:00.043 --> 32:03.544
Look, you don't have to be
the greatest mother on Earth.

32:07.083 --> 32:10.016
All you need to do for Joanie is be there.

32:12.187 --> 32:14.521
Don't ever leave her again.

32:16.724 --> 32:20.993
Stay for as long as she needs you, and...

32:20.995 --> 32:24.230
I promise you that'll be enough.

32:56.317 --> 32:59.363
_

33:12.244 --> 33:14.644
I won't have anything to do with you.

33:28.092 --> 33:30.159
Did you hear anything I just said?

33:32.497 --> 33:34.562
Yeah, you're telling me that you...

33:34.564 --> 33:37.999
I can't contact you anymore.

33:38.001 --> 33:39.167
I don't understand.

33:39.169 --> 33:40.435
How long did you leave Joanie with...

33:40.437 --> 33:41.936
Please, just don't judge me. Okay?

33:41.938 --> 33:43.571
I'm not judging you. I'm... I'm just...

33:43.573 --> 33:47.008
Well, that's why you
haven't heard from me, okay?

33:47.010 --> 33:51.778
I... I had to cut myself
off from... from everything.

33:53.682 --> 33:55.282
I had to reevaluate everything.

33:55.284 --> 33:57.684
And now that I'm back in Montauk, I'm...

33:57.686 --> 33:59.019
I'm still getting better.

33:59.021 --> 34:01.622
I'm working on myself, but I...

34:04.693 --> 34:07.827
I'm just afraid that...

34:07.829 --> 34:09.362
when you get out, you may still think

34:09.364 --> 34:11.397
you have me to come home to.

34:15.670 --> 34:18.603
And what you're trying
to tell me is I-I-I won't?

34:31.318 --> 34:33.518
What... can't we wait until I get out?

34:33.520 --> 34:34.719
It's only a few more months.

34:34.721 --> 34:36.188
No.

34:36.190 --> 34:38.121
It's been made very clear to me

34:38.123 --> 34:41.958
that if you come back into my life,

34:41.960 --> 34:44.295
I won't regain custody of Joanie.

34:55.007 --> 34:57.007
I'm sorry.

35:03.915 --> 35:07.183
She's even hotter than I
thought she'd be in real life.

35:08.019 --> 35:10.553
- What?
- Lana.

35:10.555 --> 35:12.088
She reminds me

35:12.090 --> 35:15.091
of the girls that we grew up with.

35:15.927 --> 35:16.927
You know?

35:19.263 --> 35:21.396
Hey, let it go.

35:21.398 --> 35:23.565
Not your fault.

35:23.567 --> 35:27.569
This place is like a
black hole for marriages.

35:27.571 --> 35:31.039
Goes in, don't come out.

35:31.041 --> 35:33.041
Who do you think she's fucking now?

35:33.043 --> 35:34.508
Her ex-husband?

35:34.510 --> 35:37.211
Guy that she used to work
for at that restaurant?

35:37.213 --> 35:38.379
What? Too soon?

35:39.382 --> 35:41.115
Sorry.

35:41.117 --> 35:42.617
That's what I'd be
thinking about if I was you

35:42.619 --> 35:44.218
in this place.

35:44.220 --> 35:46.621
Then again, maybe I'm
not as evolved as you are.

36:01.035 --> 36:04.704
I've been meaning to ask you...

36:04.706 --> 36:06.706
what are you here for?

36:12.045 --> 36:13.579
What did you do?

36:18.118 --> 36:20.886
I hit someone with a
car. It was an accident.

36:26.225 --> 36:27.692
You killed him?

36:29.763 --> 36:31.095
Yeah.

36:35.602 --> 36:37.702
No.

36:39.272 --> 36:43.473
People like you don't do time for that.

36:43.475 --> 36:47.010
That's weird, 'cause here you are.

36:48.514 --> 36:53.517
You must be one very
unlucky motherfucker...

36:56.154 --> 36:59.087
Or you're not telling me the whole truth.

37:01.693 --> 37:03.892
But I will find out. I always do.

37:15.806 --> 37:18.506
Hey, wait, what are you
doing? Come here! No!

37:18.508 --> 37:20.375
This is exciting. Look at this.

37:20.377 --> 37:21.876
It's not anything yet. It's just notes.

37:21.878 --> 37:23.378
Solloway.

37:23.380 --> 37:25.814
Fuck.

37:25.816 --> 37:27.281
Can I read a little bit?

37:34.457 --> 37:37.224
"Jack Hunter stood poised
on the starting block,"

37:37.226 --> 37:39.993
his head down, and his young muscles tense.

37:39.995 --> 37:42.529
The cold, hard water
from his pre-swim shower

37:42.531 --> 37:44.331
was beading on his arm hair,

37:44.333 --> 37:47.368
a thousand tiny magnifying glasses

37:47.370 --> 37:50.236
"clinging to his skin."

37:50.238 --> 37:52.505
My God.

37:52.507 --> 37:54.440
I got a hard-on.

37:59.313 --> 38:01.647
Swimming.

38:01.649 --> 38:03.649
It's beautiful, man.

38:03.651 --> 38:06.185
It's really, really beautiful.

38:06.187 --> 38:07.419
Wait,

38:07.421 --> 38:09.354
who's, who's Jack Hunter?

38:13.861 --> 38:15.994
Nobody.

38:15.996 --> 38:17.496
Just made him up.

38:22.669 --> 38:23.834
I'm gonna hang onto this, you know,

38:23.836 --> 38:25.035
just make sure that it's safe.

38:25.037 --> 38:26.103
Come on, John. It's just a story.

38:26.105 --> 38:27.705
It's Gunther!

38:31.944 --> 38:34.578
I'm gonna keep this.

38:34.580 --> 38:38.081
If anything were to happen to you,

38:38.083 --> 38:39.750
your work is safe.

38:46.224 --> 38:47.524
It's my only copy.

38:47.526 --> 38:49.225
It's my only fucking copy!

39:44.513 --> 39:46.079
Noah?

39:48.016 --> 39:49.682
- Hey.
- Hey.

39:49.684 --> 39:51.416
What are you doing out here?

39:56.023 --> 39:57.790
Nothing. I-I...

40:00.094 --> 40:02.260
thought I saw someone I knew.

40:02.262 --> 40:04.129
Someone you knew?

40:04.131 --> 40:06.063
It's 2:00 in the morning.

40:07.501 --> 40:08.867
Yeah.

40:21.147 --> 40:22.613
My dad died.

40:22.615 --> 40:24.948
Just over a week ago.

40:24.950 --> 40:27.217
He did?

40:27.219 --> 40:29.653
My God, Noah. I'm so sorry.

40:29.655 --> 40:31.522
No. It's okay.

40:31.524 --> 40:34.858
How is it okay?

40:34.860 --> 40:36.793
Well, I just meant...

40:39.297 --> 40:41.063
I don't know what I meant.

40:42.500 --> 40:45.535
Did he say good-bye?

40:45.537 --> 40:46.903
No.

40:55.980 --> 40:59.080
What do you know about your dad?

40:59.082 --> 41:01.750
I told you.

41:01.752 --> 41:03.317
Nothing.

41:03.319 --> 41:05.420
Athena must have some idea who he is.

41:05.422 --> 41:07.522
Nope. She says she doesn't.

41:09.593 --> 41:10.859
How many people could she possibly

41:10.861 --> 41:12.460
have been sleeping with at once?

41:15.031 --> 41:17.932
Yeah. I think she's lying.

41:17.934 --> 41:21.101
I actually think they were
seeing each other on and off

41:21.103 --> 41:22.770
when I was younger.

41:22.772 --> 41:27.274
You know, she'd leave a
week here, a week there.

41:27.276 --> 41:29.209
Once she left for six months.

41:35.917 --> 41:39.953
Yeah. Well, he's probably married.

41:39.955 --> 41:41.788
I'm sure you could find
him if you wanted to.

41:41.790 --> 41:43.056
And say what?

41:43.058 --> 41:45.725
"You're a shit. Thanks for nothing."

41:50.864 --> 41:53.465
What amazes me, though, is
that I spent my whole life

41:53.467 --> 41:55.901
trying not to become my mother,

41:55.903 --> 41:59.237
and, um... somehow that's...

41:59.239 --> 42:01.172
You haven't become her, Alison.

42:04.377 --> 42:05.810
Haven't I?

42:16.589 --> 42:19.056
Fires, oceans, and babies.

42:21.260 --> 42:25.361
Those are the things I could watch forever.

42:25.363 --> 42:28.197
Fires, oceans, babies.

42:42.513 --> 42:44.813
I don't know how you made
it through Gabriel's death.

42:49.620 --> 42:53.122
I thought about it a lot
when I was away, and just...

42:55.192 --> 42:58.492
29 years old, and you lose your child.

42:58.494 --> 43:00.895
No real parents, no
one to take care of you.

43:00.897 --> 43:04.065
I-I don't know how you survived.

43:04.067 --> 43:05.933
I didn't, really.

43:14.677 --> 43:17.610
Whoever I was back then, she...

43:19.548 --> 43:21.481
She died when he did.

43:31.425 --> 43:33.358
No, but I, um...

43:35.563 --> 43:37.930
I did have someone taking care of me.

43:41.569 --> 43:43.335
I had Cole.

43:57.250 --> 43:59.617
Did your dad leave you anything?

44:03.256 --> 44:05.789
Yeah... His house.

44:05.791 --> 44:07.691
What? He didn't leave it to Nina?

44:07.693 --> 44:08.959
Nope.

44:08.961 --> 44:11.528
That's weird, isn't it?

44:11.530 --> 44:13.463
Yeah, it is weird.

44:14.900 --> 44:18.869
When was the last time you were there?

44:18.871 --> 44:20.370
I don't know.

44:20.372 --> 44:22.238
Twenty years ago.

44:22.240 --> 44:24.473
You haven't been back in 20 years?

44:24.475 --> 44:25.842
Why not?

44:32.751 --> 44:35.618
My mother died there.

44:35.620 --> 44:37.319
Noah,

44:37.321 --> 44:41.156
I-I just assumed that
she died in a hospital.

44:46.329 --> 44:47.829
No, she was...

44:47.831 --> 44:49.931
She was sick for a long time.

44:51.935 --> 44:55.602
My dad couldn't handle
it. He basically left home.

44:55.604 --> 44:56.971
And Nina got out of there

44:56.973 --> 45:01.508
as soon as high school was over, so...

45:01.510 --> 45:02.509
In the end,

45:02.511 --> 45:04.779
it was just me and Ma.

45:08.584 --> 45:12.351
I remember the day I
heard I got into Williams.

45:12.353 --> 45:13.987
Full-ride.

45:17.458 --> 45:19.625
It was the worst day of my life.

45:23.098 --> 45:24.463
Why?

45:26.434 --> 45:29.968
'Cause I knew I couldn't go.

45:31.939 --> 45:35.207
I mean, who'd... who'd take
care of her if I was gone?

45:41.215 --> 45:42.314
I hid the letter.

45:42.316 --> 45:44.016
I wasn't gonna tell her, but...

45:44.018 --> 45:45.317
I was gonna pretend

45:45.319 --> 45:46.483
I didn't get in.

45:46.485 --> 45:49.287
They called the school. High school.

45:49.289 --> 45:53.657
Because that's what they do
with all the scholarship kids.

45:53.659 --> 45:56.861
And the principal called my mother, and...

45:59.866 --> 46:01.699
She was so excited.

46:06.138 --> 46:09.239
She started to cry, and then she...

46:16.815 --> 46:19.515
Then she nearly choked on her own...

46:22.854 --> 46:24.253
Noah, I'm sorry.

46:24.255 --> 46:26.255
It's a horrible disease.

46:32.263 --> 46:35.430
Anyway, it was...

46:35.432 --> 46:36.865
It was like a month before

46:36.867 --> 46:40.969
I graduated from senior year.

46:43.206 --> 46:46.640
And she told me that she'd decided to die.

46:50.280 --> 46:53.014
She was gonna... you know.

46:53.016 --> 46:54.447
What?

46:54.449 --> 46:56.216
What, for you?

46:58.420 --> 47:02.722
Well, she never said that, but...

47:02.724 --> 47:04.024
She knew about the scholarship

47:04.026 --> 47:07.127
and she knew she was alone, so...

47:09.965 --> 47:11.864
The problem was her hands.

47:11.866 --> 47:13.632
Her... her hands?

47:15.370 --> 47:16.903
Yeah, I mean, the MS,

47:16.905 --> 47:19.538
it... made them so gnarled

47:19.540 --> 47:23.475
that she... she couldn't
open the pill bottle.

47:25.046 --> 47:27.213
She couldn't even swallow the pills.

47:29.549 --> 47:31.549
So, I...

47:36.256 --> 47:39.891
So I crushed them up for her and...

47:39.893 --> 47:43.395
Mixed them with yogurt.

47:43.397 --> 47:44.729
Noah.

47:50.469 --> 47:52.970
And we spent the day together.

47:54.974 --> 47:57.308
I read to her.

47:57.310 --> 48:00.610
Just headlines and some short stories,

48:00.612 --> 48:03.913
and... her favorite poems.

48:08.186 --> 48:11.654
And then she told me I'd been a...

48:15.126 --> 48:17.493
Hey.

48:23.633 --> 48:26.835
She told me I'd been
a wonderful son, and...

48:30.841 --> 48:32.774
Then I fed the yogurt to her.

48:37.046 --> 48:41.015
Like she was my child.

48:42.618 --> 48:44.651
Noah, here.

48:46.155 --> 48:48.990
Shh.

48:57.632 --> 49:00.733
I thought about you all the time.

49:00.735 --> 49:02.502
When I was in prison, I
thought about you all the time.

49:02.504 --> 49:04.704
I kept asking myself,

49:04.706 --> 49:06.839
"What is it about her..." about you...

49:06.841 --> 49:10.542
"What..."

49:10.544 --> 49:13.545
You just the wrong
person at the wrong time?

49:13.547 --> 49:15.881
Why did I just blow up my whole life

49:15.883 --> 49:17.649
for a girl I met at a diner?

